</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-2513E5DF-C282-453D-9841-6E539DB0EB51" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Evaluate/Prevention</title><p class="- topic/p ">Adhesion testing should be done after approx.1 day. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-987F83F9-80F0-41BC-B82B-BB16DA268203" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Background info</title><p class="- topic/p ">Adhesion of ink on the media is established by curing of the ink molecules on the surface of the media.
</p><p class="- topic/p "> As the UVGel ink is not penetrating the media the surface needs to be in good condition. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">At very thick ink layers (eg: 5-layers in CMxx) also adhesion within the ink layer itself is important. 
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-945E6C60-1212-47DF-9487-92374227D4B4.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Solutions</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
